Create a data cloud¶

In [67]:
y1 = np.array([4, 2, 3], dtype=float)
y1 /= np.linalg.norm(y1)
y2 = np.array([-1, 1, 0], dtype=float)
y2 /= np.linalg.norm(y2)
In [68]:
n_points = 500
In [69]:
A = []
for k in range(n_points):
    x = 2.*np.random.randn()*y1 + np.random.randn()*y2
    A.append( x + np.random.rand(3) )
A = np.array(A)
In [70]:
np.shape(A)
Out[70]:
(500, 3)

View Data Cloud in 3-D¶

In [82]:
fig = plt.figure()
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')
ax.scatter(A[:,0], A[:,1], A[:,2], marker='.');
plt.axis('equal');
plt.title('The cloud is like an elongated pancake');

Low-Rank Approximation¶

In [77]:
k = 2

from copy import deepcopy
Sk = deepcopy(S)
Sk[2] = 0.

Ak = U @ np.diag(Sk) @ VT

3D (flattened) Data Cloud¶

In [81]:

plt.axis('equal');
plt.title('Looking at the subspace end-on');
